# IWCT Website — Core Rules

These rules apply to every conversation in this project. Keep them short. Anything longer belongs in `docs/`.

- Always use Astro + Tailwind CSS. Never use inline styles.
- Keep components small and focused — one job per component.
- Add a comment at the top of every file explaining what it does.
- Never remove existing content without confirming first.
- Follow the tone and rules in `docs/BRAND_RULES.md`.
- SEO: every page needs a unique title and meta description. **Never change titles, meta descriptions, `noindex`, canonical, or structured data without explicit user approval and a before/after summary** — see `docs/SEO_METADATA.md` and `.cursor/rules/seo-metadata.mdc`.
- Break all suggestions into small steps and confirm before proceeding.
